{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17617555","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17617555"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:14:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:14:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16474"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16474","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16474"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9165"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71200"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9165","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9165"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16474"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56674"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"39"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5230"},{"type":"tags","id":"5901"},{"type":"tags","id":"5959"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21764"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21768"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71200","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71200"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGuillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome is an acute inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy that typically develops following a preceding infection.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most appropriate as initial therapy for Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors","High-dose corticosteroids","Intravenous immunoglobulin","Plasmapheresis with steroids","Therapeutic plasma exchange alone"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous immunoglobulin\u003C/strong\u003E is one of two proven first-line treatments for Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome, the other being plasma exchange. Both treatments are equally effective when given early in the disease course.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh-dose corticosteroids\u003C/strong\u003E have not shown benefit in Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome and may worsen outcomes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcetylcholinesterase inhibitors\u003C/strong\u003E are used in myasthenia gravis but have no role in Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlasmapheresis with steroids\u003C/strong\u003E combines two treatments where one (steroids) may be harmful\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETherapeutic plasma exchange alone\u003C/strong\u003E, while effective, is often less preferred as initial therapy due to greater technical complexity and limited availability\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe choice between intravenous immunoglobulin and plasma exchange often depends on local expertise and availability. Intravenous immunoglobulin is typically preferred as initial therapy due to greater ease of administration and better availability.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Intravenous immunoglobulin and plasma exchange are equally effective first-line treatments for Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome.","Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome is an acute inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy requiring prompt treatment.","Corticosteroids are not beneficial in Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome and may worsen outcomes."],"references":["Pritchard J. Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome. Clin Med (Lond). 2010 Aug;10(4):399-401. doi: 10.7861/clinmedicine.10-4-399. PMID: 20849020; PMCID: PMC4952175","Bellanti R, Rinaldi S. Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome: a comprehensive review. Eur J Neurol. 2024 Aug;31(8):e16365. doi: 10.1111/ene.16365. Epub 2024 May 30. PMID: 38813755; PMCID: PMC11235944","Leonhard SE, Mandarakas MR, Gondim FAA, Bateman K, Ferreira MLB, Cornblath DR, van Doorn PA, Dourado ME, Hughes RAC, Islam B, Kusunoki S, Pardo CA, Reisin R, Sejvar JJ, Shahrizaila N, Soares C, Umapathi T, Wang Y, Yiu EM, Willison HJ, Jacobs BC. Diagnosis and management of Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome in ten steps. Nat Rev Neurol. 2019 Nov;15(11):671-683. doi: 10.1038/s41582-019-0250-9. Epub 2019 Sep 20. PMID: 31541214; PMCID: PMC6821638","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56674"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16474"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56674","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56674"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T19:52:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T19:53:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9165"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71200"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"32","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/32"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurosurgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null}